// C3: Physical sensing component
instance CpsMeasurementSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensor measuring physical CPS variables; readings are collected as time-series traces."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MqttDataStream
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance MqttDataStream : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "One-way MQTT protocol data stream transmitting aggregated sensor measurements to the digital twin."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CpsMeasurementSensor
]

// C10: Data
instance AggregatedContextualData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated contextual data record representing the digital shadow; derived from raw sensor traces."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MqttDataStream
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkEngine, MontiArcAutomatonEngine
]

// C10: Models
instance SimulinkPhysicsModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Physics-based white‑box model implemented in MATLAB/Simulink for dynamic simulation of the CPS."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkEngine
]

instance MachineLearningPredictionModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Data‑driven black‑box model (machine learning) used to predict CPS behavior."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo MontiArcAutomatonEngine
]

// C11: Enablers
instance SimulinkEngine : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Simulation engine executing Simulink models."
    DTDFVocab:enables DecisionSupportService
]

instance MontiArcAutomatonEngine : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Execution environment for MontiArc Automaton models and generated Java/C++ code."
    DTDFVocab:enables DecisionSupportService
]

// C6: Services
instance DecisionSupportService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service that presents computed insights to stakeholders, enabling query and visualization."
    DTDFVocab:provides DerivedPerformanceMetricInsight
]

// C17: Insight
instance DerivedPerformanceMetricInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Higher‑level abstraction (aggregated performance metrics) automatically computed from input data and models."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system is orchestrated around the Digital Shadow Reference Model, which is expressed as a UML class diagram. Core elements are Assets (physical components), Models (engineering, simulation, or data‑calculation models), Processing Components (software services that consume input data traces and produce derived data traces), and Data Traces themselves. Concretization maps these abstract concepts to concrete classes and relations, establishing a component‑centric architecture where each Processing Component encapsulates a specific computational function (e.g., simulation, data aggregation) and maintains traceability through the ‘originates‑from’ association. This structure enables systematic integration of heterogeneous models and tools (e.g., Simulink, C++, Java) and supports resource management by assigning processing workloads to dedicated computational units. System‑wide coordination is achieved by chaining Processing Components via data‑trace dependencies, allowing transitive traceability and coherent execution across the whole Twin."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle follows the MBSE development flow described in Document 1: (1) Requirements stage, where high‑level functional requirements are captured; (2) Functional‑architecture stage, modelled with SysML requirement and block diagrams; (3) Logical‑architecture stage, expressed with ADLs such as ACME, AADL, MontiArc, describing components, interfaces and connectors; (4) Product/technical stage, where the logical model is concretized into engineering models (Simulink, C++/Java code) and simulation models. Transition between stages is managed by conformance relations to the reference model (Document 2) and by concretization mappings that instantiate abstract concepts with concrete elements. Governance involves traceability of data traces back to processing components and models as defined in the Digital Shadow Reference Model."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The documents emphasize traceability and verification of model transformations (e.g., from SysML to simulation models) as essential for ensuring correctness of the Digital Twin’s underlying models and data. Reliability of the digital shadow depends on the correctness of its models and data transformations, and research highlights the need for traceability links to support verification and validation activities."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "Communication between the physical sensors and the digital shadow relies on the MQTT protocol. The MQTT publish/subscribe mechanism is used to stream time‑series sensor data from the physical layer to the digital environment. The documents do not provide further details on network topology, bandwidth, latency, redundancy, or additional security protocols."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The approach relies on modelling standards explicitly mentioned in the documents: SysML is used for requirement, block and internal‑block diagrams; UML class diagrams are employed for the Digital Shadow Reference Model; and architecture description languages—ACME, AADL and MontiArc—are used to describe component‑connector structures and, where supported, behavioural semantics (e.g., MontiArc Automaton, SysML v1.7 state machines). Conformance to these standards is enforced through a ‘conformance relation’ that identifies the set of models that correctly instantiate the reference concepts within the same modelling language."
]